---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Romania Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/romania/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Bulgaria for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/bulgaria' },
  { title: 'Hungary for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/hungary' },
  { title: 'Moldova for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/moldova' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'romaniaFit', header: 'Romania Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'RON 1,400-2,000/mo', romaniaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'RON 1,650-2,350/mo', romaniaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'RON 1,300-1,850/mo', romaniaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'RON 1,200-1,750/mo', romaniaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Romanian CNAS', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'N/A', monthlyFrom: '10% income', romaniaFit: 'For Residents' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'RON 1,300-2,000', annual: 'RON 15,600-24,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'RON 1,800-2,700', annual: 'RON 21,600-32,400' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'RON 2,400-3,600', annual: 'RON 28,800-43,200' },
  { category: 'Romanian Public (CNAS)', monthly: '10% of income', annual: 'Contribution-based' },
  { category: 'Romanian Private Clinic', monthly: 'RON 150-500', annual: 'RON 1,800-6,000' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Romania 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Romania. Affordable EU living, Transylvania, Bucharest hospitals, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Romania"
  subheadline="Romania offers dramatic Carpathian mountains, Black Sea coast, fascinating history, and very affordable EU living—with improving healthcare infrastructure."
  heroImage="/images/countries/romania-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Romania</h2>
  <p>
    Romania offers exceptional value within the EU—dramatic landscapes from Carpathian peaks to Black Sea beaches, rich culture from Transylvania's castles to painted monasteries. Cost of living is remarkably low while EU membership ensures improving standards and easy European travel.
  </p>

  <p>
    Bucharest provides cosmopolitan capital life with growing international healthcare. Transylvania's Brașov and Sibiu offer mountain charm and historic towns. The Black Sea coast delivers beach living. Timișoara and Cluj provide smaller-city appeal with good facilities.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Improving; private sector good in cities</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Romanian (Romance language); English in cities</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> RON 4,000-7,500/month (~€800-1,500); very affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Continental; hot summers, cold winters</li>
      <li><strong>EU Status:</strong> Full EU member (not yet Eurozone; uses RON)</li>
      <li><strong>Geography:</strong> Carpathians, Black Sea, Danube Delta</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Romania's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Romania has public healthcare through CNAS (National Health Insurance House) funded by social contributions. Quality in public sector varies significantly—major cities have improved, rural areas remain basic. Private healthcare has grown rapidly and provides reliable care in cities.
  </p>

  <p>
    Bucharest's private hospitals (Medlife, Regina Maria, Sanador) offer modern facilities and English-speaking staff. Private clinics exist in all major cities. Many Romanians and expats pay out-of-pocket for private care given public system limitations. Costs are fraction of Western Europe.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Public Healthcare Limitations</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Romanian public healthcare, while improving, faces challenges—outdated facilities, long waits, limited English. Many doctors have emigrated to Western Europe. Private healthcare is essential for reliable senior care. International insurance with evacuation coverage is recommended for complex conditions.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Romania offers straightforward options for retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Long-Stay Visa (Type D)</h3>
  <p>
    For those demonstrating sufficient income (typically RON 4,000+/month or €800+) and health insurance. Valid up to 1 year. Apply at Romanian embassy before arrival.
  </p>

  <h3>Temporary Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    After D visa, apply for residence permit. Requires proof of accommodation, insurance, financial means. Valid 1 year, renewable. After 5 years can apply for permanent residence.
  </p>

  <h3>EU/EEA Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Free movement applies. Register with local authorities after 90 days. Demonstrate sufficient resources and health coverage. Can access Romanian healthcare once contributing.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Romania:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Visa application:</strong> Comprehensive health insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>EU citizens:</strong> EHIC initially; can join Romanian system</li>
    <li><strong>After residence:</strong> Can voluntarily join CNAS or maintain private</li>
    <li><strong>Private recommended:</strong> Most expats prefer private healthcare quality</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Romania</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential for visa and recommended for ongoing care quality. Romanian private healthcare is affordable (RON 150-300 per consultation) for routine needs. Keep international coverage for complex care, specialists, and potential evacuation to higher-quality facilities.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Romania, these providers offer comprehensive coverage at reasonable cost:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Romania</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good European network, evacuation included</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive Eastern Europe pricing</li>
    <li><strong>Romanian Private:</strong> Medlife, Regina Maria for local care</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage and pricing from providers that accept seniors for Romania.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Romania are very affordable by EU standards:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> RON 10,000+ deductible reduces international premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Romanian private:</strong> Medlife packages from RON 200-400/month</li>
    <li><strong>Direct pay routine:</strong> Private consultations RON 150-300; affordable cash</li>
    <li><strong>CNAS backup:</strong> Join public system as secondary coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Retiree, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,800/month pension. Attracted by Transylvania and value.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care for visa and comprehensive coverage. Use Regina Maria private clinics. Lives in Brașov.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Allianz ~RON 1,500/month (~$310). Lives comfortably on remaining pension in mountain town.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Couple, Both 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Post-Brexit, seeking affordable EU with culture. Combined pension £2,400/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global for both. Living in Sibiu—historic town with good facilities.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~RON 4,000/month combined (~£700). Excellent lifestyle on remaining pension.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: German EU Citizen, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Moving from Munich to Bucharest. German pension €1,800/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> EU rights apply. Register for Romanian coverage. Add Medlife package. Cigna for Germany visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Romanian public + Medlife RON 350/month + Cigna (Romania excluded) ~€250/month.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Romania really that affordable?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—among EU's cheapest countries. A comfortable life costs RON 5,000-7,500/month (€1,000-1,500). Restaurant meals RON 30-60. Rent in cities RON 1,500-3,000. Private healthcare consultations RON 150-300. It's 60-70% cheaper than Western Europe.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Romanian hard to learn?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Romanian is a Romance language—easier than you'd think for English speakers with French, Spanish, or Italian background. Grammar is challenging but vocabulary is familiar. English is widely spoken in Bucharest and by younger Romanians. Learning basic Romanian helps significantly.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about Dracula tourism?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Transylvania is real (it means "beyond the forest") and beautiful. Bran Castle is marketed as "Dracula's Castle" but has tenuous Vlad connection. The real appeal: stunning Carpathians, fortified churches, medieval towns like Sibiu and Sighișoara, and dramatic landscapes. Very liveable region.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">When does Romania join Schengen?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Romania joined Schengen air and sea borders in March 2024. Full land border accession is expected 2025. This means easier EU travel. Romania is also working toward euro adoption, though no firm date yet. EU integration continues improving standards.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for Romania.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Romanian authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
